@junichi11 Nothing happened for almost half a year. Can we add this to a milestone?

Also, is there a checklist for adding support for a new language feature? This should've been part of 8.0 support.
If there is no such checklist may I suggest one be created to avoid such overlooks?

@junichi11 Today I was using dev build with this patch for regular development, cache was cleared before starting.
Navigation was faster than in 20-rc4 on same project.
Thank you for your work.

@czukowski Unless some critical bug is found in 20-rc4, no more changes will be merged.

@jhorvath you can restart failed jobs with the github UI on the workflow summary page without restarting the whole workflow:
![image](https://github.com/apache/netbeans/assets/114367/fb8aa4b3-ae6d-4a1e-9eb7-3b7bc0863081)

the lock/unlock trigger was only added as workaround for the case when the labels changed, since restarts via UI do not take new labels into account, since they reuse the old workflow snapshot.
